<HEADLINE> India's Sensex Closes Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The Bombay Stock Exchange
(BSE) Sensitive Index (Sensex) today settled at 3,535.52 as
against yesterday's close of 3,454.65, netting a rise of 80.87
points.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index also rose by 23.72 points to 1,532.33 from
the previous close of 1,508.61.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the Dollex were quoted up at 345.87 and 149.34
compared with yesterday's close of 340.62 and 147.87 respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
