<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loans to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank (WB) today
approved two loans to Nepal totaling 103.27 million U.S. dollars,
Nepal's official RSS news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 23.5 million dollars is to support the
multi-modal transport and trade facilitation projects, which are
expected to be completed by 2002.
</P>
<P>
The second loan of 79.77 million dollars is for a six-year
irrigation project, which will benefit some one million people,
the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The bank is a member of the Nepal Aid Group.  
</P>
</TEXT>
