<HEADLINE> Italian President Concludes Four-Day Visit to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Italian president Oscar
Luigi Scalfaro left here this afternoon for Asmara, Eritrea after
concluding his four-day official visit to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
In a press briefing here, he said his visit to Ethiopia has
been successful, and will pave the way for greater cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said, the discussions he had with Ethiopian president
Negasso Gidada and prime minister Meles Zenawi, on bilateral as
well as regional issues were very important and have created a
favourable condition for yet a greater cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro arrived here last Sunday. He is the first
Italian head of state to visit Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a press release issued by the Italian embassy here
said, the Italian government has decided the immediate dispatch
by air of medicines, tents, hand tools, motor boats and other
emergency items worth 177,000 US dollars to Ethiopia's Somali
region.
</P>
<P>
It said, this was in response to the appeal of the disaster
prevention preparedness commission of Ethiopia and the requests
from the Somali region in favour of the flood victims. 
</P>
