<HEADLINE> Jansher Knocked out of Qatar International Squash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 26 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher
Khan was knocked out of the Qatar international squash tournament
in Doha, Qatar on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jansher, seven-time World Open champion and five-time winner
of the Qatar event, lost to fourth seed Jonathon Power of Canada
in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Power won 15-14, 15-6, 15-2 to clinch his first victory over
the Pakistani.
</P>
<P>
The last game of the match took just four minutes as Jansher
was reduced to walking pace, making no effort to save the
situation. 
</P>
