<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971127.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves for Canadian City of Calgary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VANCOUVER, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin left here today for the Canadian city of Calgary, starting
his four-day state visit to Canada.
</P>
<P>
From Calgary, Jiang will travel on to Canada's capital of
Ottawa and its largest city of Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Among those seeing Jiang and his wife Wang Yeping off at the
airport were Song Youming, Chinese consular general in Vancouver,
Long Yongtu, chief negotiator of China's Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation, and Canadian officials.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage, including Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen and Minister Wu Yi of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation, left for Calgary by the same plane.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president came here last Sunday for the fifth
informal APEC (Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation) Leaders'
Meeting.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang enumerated on China's policy on the
cooperation between APEC member economies and made specific
proposals on economic and technical cooperation, one of them being
the APEC Agenda for Science and Technology Industry Cooperation
into the 21st Century.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that China will host the 9th informal APEC
Leaders' Meeting in Shanghai in the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
On the sidelines of the meeting, Jiang met with other APEC
leaders and business CEOs from the APEC economies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
