<HEADLINE> U.S. Attorney General Hospitalized in Mexico City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 26 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Attorney General Janet
Reno was hospitalized On Tuesday evening in Mexico City after
fainting briefly at a reception and is being treated for
gallstones, the Justice Department said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Reno was in Mexico City to attend a conference of Western
Hemisphere prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
The department said Reno began to feel ill on Tuesday evening
while attending a social function opening the Inter-American
Association of Public Prosecutors Conference.
</P>
<P>
The department said Reno felt nauseous and briefly fainted
before leaving the reception on her own power. She was later taken
to Estado Mayor Presidente hospital for observation where she
stayed overnight.
</P>
<P>
Doctors told Reno her problems stemmed from gallstones and
fatigue, but that she was fit enough to travel.
</P>
<P>
The Justice Department said Reno intends to travel today to
Miami where she will rest over the Thanksgiving holiday. The
department said Reno indicated this morning she was feeling fine
and looking forward to returning to work.
</P>
<P>
The White House said President Bill Clinton and Reno talked by
phone today. 
</P>
