<HEADLINE> Over 1 million Britons Get Drunk Each Week: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 26 (Xinhua) -- British people drink heavily
and believe that getting drunk is "part of the English way of
life", local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
An official survey by the Health Education Authority was quoted
as saying that nearly one million British men and 200,000 women
get drunk at least once a week.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 1,600 adults found that two-fifths of men in the
age group of 16 to 24 drink four or more pints of beer at least
once a week. 
</P>
