<HEADLINE> Support Rate of French PM Rises, That of Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The support rate for Prime
Minister Lionel Jospin rose by 7 points to 54 percent in October,
and that for President Jacques Chirac stayed stable at 46 percent,
said a poll by the CSA polling institute today.
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, 54 percent of the French people "have
confidence in Prime Minister Jospin to face up to the principal
problems which pose themselves in our country."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 35 percent of the people polled hold negative
opinions about Jospin, while 11 percent failed to answer
questions.
</P>
<P>
The support rate for Chirac remained at 46 percent, the same as
in September, while 43 percent of those polled expressed negative
opinions about him, and 11 percent failed to answer.
</P>
<P>
The poll was conducted on November 19-20 among 1,006 people
aged above 18 and representing all walks of life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
