<HEADLINE> Portuguese FM to Visit Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Foreign Minister
Jaime Gama is scheduled to arrive here this evening for an
official visit at the invitation of Mozambican Minister of
Foreign Affairs and Cooperation Leonardo Simao.
</P>
<P>
The visit comes at a time when the Portuguese cabinet had just
had a reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
"Mozambique is such an important country that even the
reshuffle of the cabinet could not stop the minister's visit,"
said Brito e Cunha, Portuguese ambassador to Mozambique in a
telephone interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming visit indicates that "the two countries share a
good relationship and a common wish that the two sides will
enhance cooperation within the framework of Portuguese-speaking
countries," Cunha said.
</P>
<P>
Gama is expected to hold talks with Foreign Minister Simao,
President Joaquim Chissano, Speaker of Parliament Eduardo
Mulembue, Prime Minister Pascoal Mocumbi and other senior
leaders.
</P>
<P>
Portugal is reportedly the No.1 investor in Mozambique, with
160 projects in the country and a direct investment of 99 million
U.S. dollars during the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
Portugal sent 30 tons of latacto de ringer to cholera patients
in Mozambique last week worth 185,000 dollars. Another 40 tons of
the medicine will arrive today and tomorrow. 
