<HEADLINE> Cyprus Welcomes Efforts on Altering Turkey's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus today welcomed the
international efforts to persuade the Turkish government to
alter its position on Cyprus issue and Cyprus' European Union
(EU) accession.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at his daily press briefing here, government
spokesman Manolis Christofides said that the Cypriot government
believes that Turkey's uncooperative position on Cyprus issue and
its EU accession have left the country isolated.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus and five other east European applicant countries are
set to start membership negotiations next year with the
EU. Turkey, which is not included in this list, has reacted
strongly to this decision which it considers discriminatory.
</P>
<P>
Turkey also seeks to become a member of the European family or
have its application for accession approved by EU's 15 member
states.
</P>
<P>
Christofides noted that the international community does not
recognize the present status quo in Cyprus and wants to redress
this by creating a bizonal, bicommunal federation.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased that efforts by the international community
to solve the Cyprus problem are now directed toward Turkey,"
Christofides said.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus problem has remained unresolved since 1974 when
Turkish troops landed and took over the northern third of the
island in the wake of a short-lived coup by Greek Cypriots
seeking union with Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
