<HEADLINE> UK-S.Africa Protocol Gives Investors Confidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 26 (Xinhua) - Britain and South Africa have
taken a major step towards ratifying an Investment Promotion and
Protection Agreement (IPPA), Department of Trade and Industry
(DTI) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
IPPAs are designed to protect and encourage UK investment in
South Africa. They contain strong commitments from overseas
governments to ensure fair treatment of investment by UK
companies.
</P>
<P>
A protocol to the IPPA with South Africa was signed on Tuesday
at the first bilateral forum between Britain and South Africa,
which enables the UK and South Africa to move towards ratification
of the IPPA in the near future, DTI said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Margaret Beckett, President
of the Board of Trade, said, "British companies look for the
existence of an IPPA when making investment decisions."
</P>
<P>
"Ratification of the agreement with South Africa will give
added confidence to British investors in South Africa," she added.
</P>
</TEXT>
