<HEADLINE> People's Daily: Promoting Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 26 (Xinhua) -- An editorial to be published
in China's official People's Daily Thursday says the APEC Approach
will promote economic and technical cooperation as well as trade
and investment liberalization in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The approach, raised by Chinese President Jiang Zemin at the
4th APEC meeting, was reiterated in the Vancouver Declaration,
adopted at the 5th APEC informal leaders' meeting in Vancouver,
Canada.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says the approach, an "entirely new approach" to
international economic cooperation, gives full consideration to
the diversity of APEC members and acknowledges their divergence in
the level and state of development as well as the consequent
differing interests and needs.
</P>
<P>
The approach also adheres to the principles of mutual respect,
equality, mutual benefit, consensus, seeking common ground while
putting aside differences and voluntarism, the editorial adds.
</P>
<P>
This is in conformity with the trend of the time and the actual
circumstances in the region.
</P>
<P>
APEC (Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) is the most
influential economic forum in the region and one of the most
vigorous organizations for economic cooperation in the world.
</P>
<P>
The editorial continues that under the approach, trade and
investment liberalization will be carried out through both
unilateral and team actions so as to achieve common development
and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
It says the informal leaders' meeting, which concluded
successfully Tuesday, will promote economic and trade cooperation
as well as technological exchange among the APEC members.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang made an important speech at the meeting. Before
it, a ministerial meeting was held on expanding economic and
technical cooperation, setting up relevant cooperation mechanism,
improving advance liberalization in partial sectors and promoting
regional financial cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
