<HEADLINE> Finnish Leader Visits Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Finnish President
Martti Ahisaari expressed satisfaction with the fact that Russia
speedily signed border treaties with Estonia and Latvia, according
to the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference the Finnish President, who arrived in
Moscow this afternoon on a two-day visit, said that the step
"would promote confidence between Russia and Baltic countries."
</P>
<P>
Referring to the security guarantees offered by Russia to the
Baltic states, Ahisaari said that he "respects the right of each
Baltic state to decide security matters on its own."
</P>
<P>
The visiting president meanwhile called on Russia and the
Baltic states to demonstrate "patience and understanding".
</P>
<P>
Speaking about relations between Russia and Finland, he said
past experience "should not hinder business cooperation between
two European countries."
</P>
<P>
Ahisaari is expected to meet Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin on Thursday. The two sides
will discuss transport between the two countries, which has
increased five-fold since Finland's admission to the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
The other subject will be the transit of Russian oil across
Finland to Western Europe, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
