<DOCNO> XIE19971127.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Adopts Action Plan to Promote Renewable Energy Uses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s
executive body, the European Commission, today adopted a white
paper on its renewable energy blueprint.
</P>
<P>
The white paper set out for the first time a comprehensive
strategy and action plan designed to achieve by 2010 the goal of
doubling the share of renewable energies from the present 6
percent to 12 percent in the EU's total energy demand.
</P>
<P>
"We are sending a clear message that we are determined to
follow an ambitious and realistic policy to promote the use of
energy sources which enhance our security of supplies, contribute
to the creation of jobs and help us protect the environment," said
Christos Papoutsis, EU commissioner responsible for energy.
</P>
<P>
The benefits from the achievement of the goal would be "very
considerable" in terms of carbon dioxide emission reduction, jobs
creation, increased security of supply and local and regional
development, the commission noted in a press release issued today.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that a central aim of the strategy and
action plan was to ensure that the need to promote renewable
energy sources was integrated in new policy initiatives as well as
in the full implementation of a wide range of policies.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the adoption of the white paper would give EU
negotiators "additional ammunition" at the upcoming United Nations
Climate Summit in Kyoto, Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
