<HEADLINE> European Shares up on Asian Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
all made moderate gains Wednesday and ended higher, boosted by
Asian markets' rebound.
</P>
<P>
Leading British shares in London finished higher but off their
best levels of the session as Wall Street reversed early gains.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index ended 27.7 points up at 4,891.2 and failed
to secure the 4,900-point level in lacklustre trading ahead of the
US Thanksgiving holiday break.
</P>
<P>
Shares in HSBC jumped by three percent as the Hong Kong market
was cheered by a recovery in Japan overnight.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the DAX-30 index was the best European performer,
which closed 1.75 percent higher, pulled by overnight gains on
Wall Street and an improved showing on Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
The index closed up 67.3 points at 3,916.53. Volumes were thin
ahead of Thursday's Thanksgiving holiday in America.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, the CAC-40 index ended 25.39 points up at
2,811.65. The market also drew support from advances in Far
Eastern markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
