<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 175 Lives in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A mobile station has been established to take in cholera
patients, and more such stations are expected to be
established.
</P>
<P>
Nampula Province and Tete Province in northern Mozambique
have prepared medicine, done publicity against the out-break of
the disease.
</P>
<P>
Some international institutions have offered some aid to
the country to help it curb the disease.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique was seriously hit by cholera in 1991 and 1992. The
disease which was first discovered in August this year seems
spreading rapidly because of the hot and humid wether. 
