<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Attend Malaysian Arms Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 26 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's arms
manufacturer Denel will participate in this year's arms show in
Malaysia, company
official said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is scheduled for December 2 to 6.
</P>
<P>
Denel Communications Director, George Masoek, told reporters in
Pretoria that his company decided to go there although many companies,
including some from the United States, Australia, Russia and Belgium,
had withdrawn from the Langkawi Aerospace and Maritime Exhibition
(LIMA).
</P>
<P>
"Although the slowdown of the Malaysian economy has resulted in a
number of the country's defense purchases being put on hold,... our
cooperation with Malaysia still continues," Masoek said.
</P>
<P>
Denel is confident the Malaysian economy will recover.
</P>
<P>
Masoek said Denel is not only interested in selling its goods, but
also in developing long-term business relationships through the
sharing of expertise.
</P>
<P>
To underline this message, South African Public Enterprises
Minister Stella Sigcau and Defense Minister Joe Modise will also
attend the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to gear both the local and Malaysian industries with
capabilities for developing, producing and supporting the Rooivalk
(attack helicopter), and in the future, other aircraft like the Oryx
transport helicopter," Masoek said.
</P>
<P>
Masoek said three of the company's divisions will participate in
the exhibition, which would focus on showing off the Rooivalk.
</P>
<P>
Other products to be displayed included the Leo multi-weather
airborne observation system and the Seeker unmanned aerial vehicle
surveillance system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
