<BODY>
<HEADLINE> London Gold Price Fixes at 12.5-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The gold price fixed today at
under 300 US dollars an ounce on the London market for the first
time in 12.5 years and analysts said it could head still lower.
</P>
<P>
It was fixed at 297 dollars per ounce in the morning and the
afternoon, and closed at 297.25 dollars versus 301.25 dollars on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy selling by investment funds in New York following the
expiry of December gold options last night sent the price close to
300 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Further sales in Asia against the weak yen and Australian
dollar took gold below the psychological barrier before European
market opened.
</P>
<P>
"There is no reason to be bullish about gold until it is clear
what the European central banks are going to do (about their gold
reserves)" said one dealer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
