<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 15:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Releases 500 Iraqi POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran today unilaterally
released 500 Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) captured during the
eight-year (1980-1988) war between the two neighbors, the
official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The POWs would be delivered to the Iraqi side on the border
this afternoon, according to an Iranian source.
</P>
<P>
The POWs were released after Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei Wednesday expressed his agreement with the proposal
put forward by President Mohammad Khatami on the issue.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony held here this morning, head of the Iranian
Commission in charge of POW Affairs Brigadier General Abdollah
Najafi said that Tehran has so far released 49,196 Iraqi POWs, of
whom 10,000 have been released unilaterally by Iran.
</P>
<P>
Najafi expressed hope that Iran's humanitarian measure
would be a preamble to the final conclusion of the POW issue
between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Iranian authorities announced that some 15,000
Iranian POWs were still held in Iraq and accused the Iraqi
government of making no response to Iran's humanitarian measures
of releasing Iraqi POWs.
</P>
<P>
However, the Iraqi side repeatedly dismissed the allegation of
any Iranian POWs in Iraq. Charge D'affaires of the Iraqi Embassy
in Iran Salah Noori Samarmad claimed earlier this month that Iraq
has released all Iranian POWs.
</P>
<P>
He said Baghdad holds 62 Iranians who were captured in Iraq
after the 1991 Gulf War, adding that "we are ready to release
these 62 Iranians if the Iranian authorities release all of our
POWs."
</P>
<P>
An estimated one million people were killed in the eight-year
war between Iran and Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
