<HEADLINE> HK's Entreport and Import Trade Up in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
entreport and import trade recorded notable increases last month
over a year earlier, while that of domestic export rose further,
official figures showed today.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures released by the Census and Statistics
Department, the value of total export trade (comprising entreport
trade and domestic export) in October rose by 10 percent over a
year earlier to 143 billion HK dollars (about 18.3 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the total, the value of entreport trade grew by 11 percent
to 122.9 billion HK dollars (about 15.8 billion U.S. dollars),
while the value of domestic export increased by 3.1 percent to 20
billion HK dollars (about 2.6 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the value of import trade increased by 11 percent to
 152.9 billion HK dollars (about 19.6 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A visible trade deficit of 10 billion HK dollars (about 1.3
billion U.S. dollars) was recorded in October compared with 8.2
billion HK dollars (about 1.1 billion U.S. dollars) a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
For the first 10 months of 1997 as a whole, the value of total
export business increased by 3.8 percent over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of entreport trade rose by 4.6 percent, while that of
 domestic export dropped by 0.7 percent. The value of import
business registered an increase of 5.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
During January-October of this year, a visible trade deficit of
137.5 billion HK dollars (about 17.6 billion U.S. dollars) was
recorded, compared with 110.3 billion HK dollars (about 14.1
billion U.S. dollars) in the same period of 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
