<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Simplifies Customs Procedures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The Kazakh Customs announced
Wednesday to simplify the checking procedure for passengers
entering or leaving Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Under the new measure, travelers need not to declare goods
traveling with them at the Customs office unless they carry
contrabands or goods for commercial purpose, the Kazakhstan Pravda
newspaper today quoted Colonel Evgenij Kachkayev from the Customs
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The measure, which was only applicable to the Kazakh citizens
last year, covers passenger of all categories so as to help
strengthen people-to-people exchanges between Kazakhstan and other
countries, Kachkayev added
</P>
<P>
This does not mean that Kazakhstan will slacken its efforts to
combat international smuggling, he added, and regulations
concerning commercial goods as well as entry-exit fees will remain
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh Customs is to adopt measures to simplify procedures
for goods of commercial purpose next year, the colonel
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
