<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Spain's minister of sport Pedro
Martin Thursday criticized the Spanish first division referees'
decision to go on strike this weekend.
</P>
<P>
"The measures taken are disproportionate and not beneficial
to a climate of dialogue," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Spanish referees have gone on strike in response to the
torrents of abuse heaped upon them in recent weeks by players
and club officials.
</P>
