<HEADLINE> Chinese Folk Arts Festival Staged in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 27 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Folk Arts Festival
is being held here, the fourth theme festival in the Chinese
culture series.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Provisional Regional Council, the festival is
bringing to the public the traditional folk art of six ethnic
groups in China in the form of stage performances, festival fairs
and free outdoor entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The festival is aimed at introducing to Hong Kong people the
cultural customs of the Han people and five ethnic groups
including the Dong, Miao, Tibetan, Korean and Tu people in China,
following the success of the last theme festival, the Chinese
Folk Culture Festival, held in 1995, according to the council.
</P>
<P>
A total of 45 performances are expected to be given during the
festival between November 22 and 30 by eight performing groups
from the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Famous folk artists from northwest China's Shaanxi Province,
will demonstrate paper-cuts, shadow puppets and wooden masks at
an arts fair. 
