<HEADLINE> Singapore Port to Handle 14 Million TEUs in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The Port of Singapore
Authority (PSA) Corporation Limited said today that it is on track
to handle 14 million TEUs (Twenty-foot Equivalent Units) in 1997,
as the port handled 1.27 million TEUs in October.
</P>
<P>
It said that a healthy growth of 12 percent in container
throughput volume had been achieved in October and with this
growth maintained, the PSA is to achieve 14 million TEUs by the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The October figure has also surpassed the previous record of
1.25 million TEUs set in July this year.
</P>
<P>
"As a corporation, we are optimistic that 1998 will continue to
be a good year for the PSA. We are confident that our services
will continue to attract customers, and that we will maintain our
status as the leading transshipment hub in the region," Ng Chee
Keong, president of the PSA's Container Terminal Division, said.
</P>
<P>
The PSA will continue to set high standards of productivity by
working closely with the customers to increase productivity so
that the port can share the gains with the customers, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
