<HEADLINE> Russia, Finland Reach 3 Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and visiting Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari today signed three
agreements on cooperation after their talks, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreements include two MOU on Finland providing Russia with
loans worth 400 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The third document is an intergovernmental protocol on Russian
companies' further work on increasing and preserving the fish
population in Lake Inari.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, Russia's Kolenergo company is to supply
electric power to Finland until 2005 year.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Yeltsin told the press in the
Kremlin that Ahtisaari's visit was "very successful."
</P>
<P>
"The dialogue between our countries must continue and our
relations must be discussed by both sides," the Russian president
said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin believed that the trade turnover between the two
countries is increasing.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish president arrived in Moscow Wednesday on a two-day
official visit to Russia. 
</P>
