<HEADLINE> Pele Voted Greatest Player of All Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian legend Pele was
declared the best footballer of all time after topping a poll of
500,000 people from 110 countries and regions as the first
entrants to the International Football Hall of Fame were announced
on Thursday, according to reports from Manchester.
</P>
<P>
Wayward Northern Ireland genius George Best, who never played
in the World Cup finals, was in second place ahead of Sir Bobby
Charlton, Dutch legend Johan Cruyff and former England skipper
Bobby Moore.
</P>
<P>
Pele won the World Cup with Brazil in 1958, 1962 and 1970, and
was the star of one of the most exciting sides ever.
</P>
<P>
Pele said: "To be chosen in a public vote by more than 500,000
people from around the globe as the No.1 player of all time is
wonderful.
</P>
<P>
"My thanks to all those who have supported me over the years
and all those who have voted me into the International Football
Hall of Fame."
</P>
<P>
In order to be eligible for the Hall of Fame, which is to be
built in Manchester next year, players had to be internationals
and been retired for at least three years.
</P>
<P>
The five players who received the most votes were automatically
admitted. The remaining 20 places have been decided in the last
week by footballers themselves and sports journalists.
</P>
<P>
The 20 were Gordon Banks, Marco van Basten, Franz Beckenbauer,
John Charles, Kenny Dalglish, Duncan Edwards, Eusebio, Tom Finney,
Garrincha, Jairzinho, Stanley Matthews, Gerd Muller, Michel
Platini, Ferenc Puskas, Roberto Rivelino, Alfredo di Stefano, Lev
Yashin, Billy Wright, Zico and Dino Zoff.
</P>
<P>
Also announced today were the five players who will hold the
title of "Future Hall of Famer" for a year.
</P>
<P>
These are current footballers and were chosen entirely by the
public. They are Diego Maradona, Alan Shearer, Ronaldo, George
Weah and David Beckham.
</P>
<P>
There will be an awards ceremony for all those chosen in the
New Year, when the full details of the Hall of Fame will be
announced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
