<HEADLINE> Industrial Project Built in Coastal Province (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To ensure the smooth implementation of this huge industrial
project, Xiaocuo is speeding up infrastructure construction. Three
oil beths accommodating 5,000-ton, 3,000-ton and 2,000-ton ships
are now in operation. Work is well under way on an oil wharf, a
multi-function coal wharf, a grain transit dock and a container
dock at a cost of 920 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Completion of these projects will turn Xiaocuo into one of four
international transit ports in China.
</P>
<P>
The zone has also allocated 1 billion yuan to build a water
diversion project at the southern bank of Meizhou Gulf, which
should be completed next month.
</P>
<P>
Other infrastructure projects include three power transmission
stations, a thermal power plant with an installed capacity of 1.9
million kilowatts at a cost of 18.9 billion yuan, two
telecommunications centers and a 100,000-line program-controlled
telephone switchboard.
</P>
<P>
So far, an oil-refining expansion project with an additional
output of 4 million tons has started trial operation. Work on the
70,000-ton polypropylene project, which will cost 700 million
yuan, is proceeding smoothly and is expected to be completed next
year.
</P>
<P>
Xiaocuo Management Committee, established in April of 1996, has
organized 10 massive trade fairs in Singapore and such major
Chinese cities as Hainan, Shenzhen and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The economic zone has approved 19 foreign-funded firms in the
first eight months of this year with a foreign investment of 17.38
million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
