<HEADLINE> Professors Join Shareholding Company in Ningbo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Twelve university professors in
the east China port city of Ningbo recently joined a shareholding
company. Some of them are on the board of directors.
</P>
<P>
The professors, all from the computer department of Ningbo
University, are now stockholders of a computer training and
service company, which is a joint venture between the university
and Meilemen Corp. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"We are holding the company's stocks for a better combination
of science and commerce," said associate professor Wang Rangding,
vice dean of the computer department. "It is also an attempt to
find a better use of our knowledge."
</P>
<P>
The computer department holds 18 percent of the company's
shares, while the rest are in the hands of the commercial
corporation and other social investors.  
