<HEADLINE> Leading Universities Form Presidents' Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of China's 10
leading universities gathered at the prestigious Fudan University
here today to form an association, which they said would promote
academic exchanges between the country's institutions of higher
education.
</P>
<P>
The 10 universities are Qinghua University, Shanghai Jiaotong
University, Beijing University, Xi'an Jiaotong University, Fudan
University, Nanjing University, City University of Hong Kong,
Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong University of Science
and Technology, and Zhejiang University.
</P>
<P>
The presidents are, respectively: Wang Dazhong, Xie Shengwu,
Chen Jiaer, Jiang Deming, Yang Fujia, Jiang Shusheng, Cheng
Yiu-chung, Arthur Li Kwok-cheung, Woo Chia-wei, and Pan Yunhe.
</P>
<P>
At the first council meeting today, Fudan University President
Yang Fujia was elected chairman, while Wang Dazhong of Qinghua
University and Arthur Li Kwok-cheung of the Chinese University of
Hong Kong were elected vice chairmen.
</P>
<P>
The association will have liaison offices in Shanghai's Fudan
University, Beijing's Qinghua University and the Chinese
University of Hong Kong.  
</P>
