<HEADLINE> France-Funded Wastewater Project Started in Nanning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction started today
on the Langdong Wastewater Disposal Plant in Nanning, capital of
the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
It is the first wastewater project in Nanning funded by
France. The French government is providing 4.95 million
U.S. dollars to build the project, while the local government
allocated 130.7 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
