<HEADLINE> Shandong Accelerates Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
has witnessed the rapid development of infrastructure
construction, formerly a bottleneck impeding local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Since early last year, the province has allocated over 30
billion yuan to build 24 key projects in the transportation,
energy, raw materials and agricultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years alone, the province has added 3.2
million kw to its installed generating capacity, extended
railway lines by 280 km and highways by 220 km, and increased the
handling capacity of local harbors by 4.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The province has also dramatically increased its production
capacity for coal, crude oil and cement.
</P>
<P>
The province has worked hard to improve local infrastructure
construction by placing priority to energy, transportation, raw
materials, agricultural and water conservancy sectors,
</P>
<P>
Plans also call for strengthening economic development in
western parts of the province, with priority placed on railway and
highway construction in central and western areas of the province,
and harbor construction in the province's eastern coastal areas.
</P>
