<HEADLINE> Price Index of Macao Construction Materials Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The price index of most
construction materials in Macao dropped a little bit in the third
quarter from the previous three months.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that the price index of aluminum, concrete,
lumber, porcelain products, toilet equipment and cement declined
by 0.3 to 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The general index went down by 0.1 percent from the previous
quarter, but it grew 0.1 percent compared with the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
The price index of steel, red bricks, glass and paint rose by
between 0.1 percent and 4.2 percent while that of sand, lime,
macadam and pipes remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The price index of glass registered the biggest increase of 4.2
percent and that of aluminum the biggest drop of 0.9 percent from
the previous quarter.  
</P>
</TEXT>
