<HEADLINE> HK's Oldest Retailer Opens New Store </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Sincere, one of Hong Kong's
oldest retailers, opened its seventh department store here today
despite a slump in the local retail business in recent months.
</P>
<P>
Covering a total floor space of 2,300 square meters in a
newly-built commercial complex in Mongkok, Kowloon, the new store
offers men's and ladies' wear, shoes, handbags, accessories,
cosmetics and crystals.
</P>
<P>
Mongkok, a densely-populated area where the Kowloon-Canton
Railway and the subway meet, has a significant potential in
consumer spending, said Philip Ma, managing director of Sincere
Group, at the opening ceremony of the new store.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Although the recent slowdown in tourism and decrease
in local consumption are undermining Hong Kong's retail sector, we
are confident that the downturn will only be temporary."
</P>
<P>
"The opening of the seventh store reflects our confidence in
Hong Kong's long-term economic prospects as well as our commitment
to the retail business," said Ma.
</P>
<P>
Founded and owned by the Ma family, Sincere set up its first
department store in Hong Kong in 1900 and has since evolved into a
diversified group with retail outlets and property interests in
Hong Kong and inland areas of China.  
</P>
