<HEADLINE> HK Personages Awarded Cultural Exchange Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Shaw Run Run and D. H. Chen,
both well-known Hong Kong personages, received here today the
cultural exchange award from the Chinese Ministry of Culture.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Junsheng, deputy director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong
Kong Branch, conferred upon them medals and citations on behalf of
the ministry in recognition of their outstanding contributions to
promoting cultural exchanges between China's inland areas and
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Shaw, chairman of the Shaw Brothers (HK) Ltd., and Chen,
chairman of the Nan Fung Textiles Ltd., won the award together
with three foreigners, two from Japan and one from Germany, during
China's Fifth National Art Festival held in Chengdu, capital of
Southwest China's Sichuan Province, last month.
</P>
<P>
At today's awarding ceremony, Shao and Chen expressed their
readiness to continue their efforts and push forward cultural
exchanges and cooperation between the mainland and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The award, the first of its kind especially set up by the
ministry, is given to those from foreign countries, the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan who have made
outstanding contributions to cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Shaw and Chen have donated more than 40 million Hong Kong
dollars to the country for relics protection and cultural and arts
development.  
</P>
