<DOCNO> XIE19971127.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Gets Fewer New Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 549 new companies
were established in the first three quarters of this year, 0.7
percent less than in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that those new companies have a total registered
capital of 120 million patacas (about 15.2 million U.S. dollars),
down 39.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of new companies established in the third quarter
alone was 171, with a combined registered capital of 59.3 million
patacas (about 7.5 million dollars). The amount of capital was
29.9 percent more than the same quarter of last year and 69.8
percent more than the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say the increase in capital in the third quarter may
be a sign of a slow recovery of the economy from a three-year
slowdown.
</P>
<P>
Of the newly-established firms, 42.1 percent are wholesale and
retail and trading businesses, restaurants and hotels while others
are involved in construction and public engineering and the
service sector.
</P>
<P>
Of the new companies established in the third quarter, nearly
90 percent were small ones, each with a registered capital of
100,000 patacas (12,666 dollars) or less and most of their capital
came from local residents.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 17 companies with a registered capital of 2.64
million patacas (about 334,000 dollars) were disbanded between
July and September. They were in businesses such as manufacturing,
construction and civil engineering, wholesale and retail,
restaurants and hotels.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
