<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Extends Loan to Vietnam for Power System Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a concessional loan of 100 million U.S.
dollars for a power distribution project in Central and Southern
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here, the bank said the project will
expand and reinforce the distribution system of two major
networks, bringing power to 70,000 new consumers, including many
living in poor rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is due for completion by June 2002, will
cost 140 million dollars, the ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The joint executing agencies -- Vietnam's Power company No.2
and No.3 -- will contribute 40 million dollars, it said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan is interest-free and carries a service charge of 1
percent annually. It is repayable over 40 years, including a grace
period of 10 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
