<HEADLINE> Uganda AIDS Commission Appeals for Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Uganda AIDS Commission (UAC)
appealed for funds, "The Monitor" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Omwony Ojwok, the UAC director-general, said his organization
has run out of funds.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national consensus workshop on the strategic
framework for HIV/AIDS activities in Uganda held on November 24,
the UAC official underlined the need to create a function to
mobilize the fund for the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
The UAC has a good reputation for its dealing with the
epidemic, Ojwok said. But still, there is a need for commitment
of resources, involvement of all stake holders, a five-year
common platform and a need to come up with a strategic framework
from 1998 to 2002, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Sponsoring the opening ceremony, Jaberi Bidandi Ssali, the
local government minister, underlined the need to deal with the
adverse impact of the epidemic because it leads to loss of highly
skilled elite of the society. 
