issues.
</P>
<P>
The news that the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) is
mapping out emergency measures to use taxpayers' money to help
banks bailout bad loans buoyed the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Comments made by the Bank of Japan governor and the finance
minister Wednesday also were taken as positive factors, leading
the key Nikkei index to stay in the positive column, traders said.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the U.S. dollar held steady at
the lower 127 yen level.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. currency was quoted at 127.11-13 yen at 5 p.m., down
from 127.20-22 yen at 9 a.m. in Tokyo, but slightly up from
126.95-127.05 yen late Wednesday in New York. 
