<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Loan to China to Improve Xiamen Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) announced here today that it has approved a 50 million U.S.
dollar loan to China to improve the Xiamen Port.
</P>
<P>
With the ADB loan, the strategically-located port of Xiamen in
China's Fujian Province will be expanded, it said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank said the project will expand the port's
break-bulk and bulk cargo handling capacity and rationalize its
cargo handling operations to meet increasing demand from the
growth of the Xiamen Special Economic Zone and provide market
access to resource-rich but less-developed neighboring inland
provinces.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan will carry an interest rate to be determined in
accordance with the bank's pool-based variable lending system for
dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is repayable over 24 years, including a four-year grace
period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the ADB will provide a technical assistance grant
of 575,000 dollars, financed by the Japan Special Fund, to help
restructure the Xiamen Harbor Bureau.  
</P>
