<HEADLINE> Nigerian Air Force Plane Crash-Lands, Kills Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 27 (Xinhua) -- An Air Beetle plane of the
Nigeria Air Force crash-landed on Tuesday during an air display,
killing a squadron leader pilot, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened in Kaiji, Niger State, where the Air
Force Weapons School is located.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the air display was arranged for this year's
air force meeting, which opened in Kaiji Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Three Alpha jets and seven air beetles took part in the air
display, during which one of the air beetles crash-landed. The
plane was reportedly safe, but the pilot sustained serious
injuries.
</P>
<P>
The squadron leader, whose name was not identified, was later
rushed to a hospital in Kaduna State, where he died on Tuesday
night.
</P>
<P>
Air Beetle was produced in Nigeria by a joint venture between
the Nigeria Air Force and the Aero Industries Engineering Project
Ltd. The factory was commissioned in 1988 by former president
General Ibrahim Babangida.
</P>
<P>
The plane involved in the accident was purchased by the air
force in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
