<HEADLINE> Sharif Promises Voting Right to Overseas Pakistanis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif said here today that overseas Pakistanis would soon
get the right to vote in the country's general elections.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the first-ever Overseas Pakistanis Convention held
here this morning, Sharif stressed that overseas Pakistanis should
have the right of voting.
</P>
<P>
Overseas Pakistanis are playing an important role in the
economic development of Pakistan, Sharif said, adding that their
demand for the voting right is quite genuine.
</P>
<P>
"We are seriously concerned about the delays in the procedure
to grant the voting right to them," Sharif said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Foreign Ministry and the Election Commission of
Pakistan, along with other relevant departments, have been busy
finalizing the necessary arrangements.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Sharif said his government would provide
overseas Pakistanis with investment opportunities in the country's
industrial and infrastructure sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said industrial zones would be created along the
333-kilometer long Islamabad-Lahore highway, which he said would
be extended from Lahore, provincial capital of Punjab, to the
southern port city of Karachi.
</P>
<P>
The government is determined to stamp out terrorism and
sectarianism to create a conducive environment for foreign and
domestic investment, Sharif added.  
</P>
