<HEADLINE> 7,350 HIV/AIDS Carriers Detected In Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's National AIDS
Committee reported today that this country had detected 7,350
HIV/AIDS carriers by November 22.
</P>
<P>
These figures may only account for 10 percent of the actual
number, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Only four of the country's 61 provinces and cities have not
reported HIV/AIDS cases.
</P>
<P>
At present, the city of Ho Chi Minh has the largest number of
HIV cases with 2,427. It is followed by the northern province of
Quang Ninh, the southern coastal provinces of Khanh Hoa and An
Giang with 400 cases each, and Hanoi with 56 cases.
</P>
<P>
The HIV-positive cases were found not only in big cities,
industrial zones and tourist resorts but also in rural, highlands
and remote mountain areas.
</P>
<P>
Identified-HIV carriers were not only drug addicts and
prostitutes, but included school and university students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
