<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda to Produce Instant Coffee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is interested in
producing instant coffee, "The People" quoted a senior official
as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Abel Rwendeire, the state minister for trade and industry,
told Allain Gauze, the president of Inter-Africa Coffee
Organization (IACO) and the trade minister of Cote d'Ivoire at a
meeting that Uganda has a two-year plan to attract foreign
investors to create the value adding industry.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held during 37th annual assembly of the
Inter-Africa Coffee Organization between November 24 and 26.
</P>
<P>
Almost all coffee producing countries except Uganda export
instant coffee, and Uganda hoped to join them in producing the
value added goods and has its own impact on the international
market within two years, the state minister noted.
</P>
<P>
Coffee earns 65 percent of foreign exchange for Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Allain gauze called upon all African coffee producing
countries to form a consortium and start exporting instant coffee
so as to have an impact on the international market.
</P>
<P>
His country produces about 20,000 tons of both instant and
non-processed coffee a year, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Cote d'Ivoire are the first two main coffee
producing countries in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
