<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Drops to Four Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar shot
down through 0.6800 US dollars in the afternoon trading today to
hit a new four year low.
</P>
<P>
The currency settled at 68.06 US cents, almost half a US cent
lower than 68.55 late yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Heavy selling against the Japanese yen sparked the move, and
the local unit bottomed at 67.93 US cents in the second half of
the session.
</P>
<P>
That marked a new low for the Australian dollar for 1997 after
it reached 68.18 US cents last month and the lowest level since
January 1994.
</P>
<P>
Paul Macarounas, treasury manager of Rothschild Australia, said
the selling had come on top of already bearish factors for the
Australian dollar, including the deepening crisis in Asia, falling
gold prices and much lower-than-expected private capital
expenditure figures released today.
</P>
<P>
Against the yen, the local currency closed at 86.55 from 87.15.
 Against the mark, the Australian dollar was at 1.2011 from
1.1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
