<HEADLINE> Uganda Coffee Export to Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Uganda coffee export is
expected to decline from 4.15 million bag last financial year to
4 million bags this financial year, "The People" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The decline is resulted from El Nino phenomenon, the paper
quoted a local specialist as saying.
</P>
<P>
Each bag contains 60 kilograms of coffee.
</P>
<P>
The overall coffee export earning of the country decreased
from 358.3 million U.S. Dollars in 1995/1996 to 336.6 million in
1996/1997, an earlier report from Uganda Coffee Development
Authority said.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports are expected to reach 5.0 million bags in
1999/2000 financial year during which the high yielding clonal
robusta coffee planted now will mature, local experts said.
Coffee is the main foreign exchange earner of Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
