<HEADLINE> Eeastern Chinese Port Increasing Trade With Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The port of Xiamen, in east
China's Fujian Province, has 84 Japanese-funded companies with
direct investment of 320 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Japanese-backed businesses are in electronics, foodstuff,
garment manufacturing, and real estate development. Most are
solely Japanese-backed and 70 percent of their products are for
export.
</P>
<P>
Japan's six leading companies all have offices in this port
city, and Japanese financial institutions have provided 132
million U.S. dollars in loans for urban infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Trade between Xiamen and Japan has been increasing yearly. In
1996, Japan was Xiamen's second largest trade partner, and its
state-owned businesses did 570 million U.S. dollars in trade with
Japan last year.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen exports processed stones, aquatic products, and textiles
to Japan and mainly imports electronic products and machinery.
</P>
