<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Takes Sterner Measure Against Illegal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Zambian immigration officers
have been empowered to arrest without warrant any people
suspected to be illegal immigrant or contravening the new
immigration and deportation act.
</P>
<P>
An immigration officer with a court warrant may enter any
premises suspected to have evidence in connection with a
contravention of the act, Times of Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
Any person visiting Zambia, whom an immigration officer
suspects to have committed an offense under the immigration and
deportation act, shall give his name and address to an
immigration officer on request.
</P>
<P>
An immigration officer may, without a warrant, arrest any
person if the person refuses or fails to furnish the immigration
officer with his name and address, said the act.
</P>
<P>
An immigration officer who facilitates the entry into Zambia
of any person in contravention of the act will be liable to a
fine or imprisonment of up to three years or both. 
</P>
</TEXT>
