<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Robots Get Special Clothing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Fifty robots on an automobile
assembly line in Shanghai, China's largest industrial city, are
dressed in special clothing thanks to the Shanghai Knitwear Mill.
</P>
<P>
Many computer-operated robots have been used by large
manufacturers in the city in recent years, doing difficult and
dangerous work that they perform better than humans do.
</P>
<P>
In order to protect the expensive robots and prolong their
life, they have been provided with special clothing, which used to
be imported in the past at high cost.
</P>
<P>
The 50 new suits are the first of their kind, four times the
size of normal clothing, and made of dust-proof knitted fabric.
