<HEADLINE> Pak to Provide Housing Facilities for Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif said today that the government would provide housing
facilities and a pension scheme for overseas Pakistanis.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the first-ever Overseas Pakistanis Convention held
here this morning and attended by more than 300 participants from
abroad, Sharif said that the government would provide 10,000 plots
to overseas Pakistanis in different cities of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said the government had already instructed the Capital
Development Authority to allocate a full sector in the federal
capital for overseas Pakistanis.
</P>
<P>
With the finalization of all arrangements, he added, overseas
Pakistanis would be invited to submit their applications for a
housing plot in Islamabad and special care would be taken to
ensure that the sector would be developed according to the needs
of overseas Pakistanis.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also said that a majority of overseas Pakistanis have no
social security coverage either in the country of employment or at
home.
</P>
<P>
To meet this need, the government is introducing a pension
scheme which will extend coverage to the needy such as the old and
the disabled, Sharif said.
</P>
<P>
There is no such pension in the country for overseas Pakistanis
at present, according to the prime minister.  
</P>
