<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Observe World AIDS Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia will observe
this year's World AIDS Day on December 1, 1997 with emphasis on
protecting children from contracting the deadly disease, the
Organizing Committee of the Anti-AIDS Campaign has announced.
</P>
<P>
According to "The Ethiopian Herald" today, at a panel
discussion held at the Ministry of Health on Wednesday, Ayele
Belachew, chairman of the Organizing Committee, said this year's
World AIDS Day will be observed throughout the country under the
theme "children living in a world with AIDS".
</P>
<P>
He noted that the event will involve the public through
different participatory activities.
</P>
<P>
The spread of the HIV-AIDS in the world and Ethiopia in
particular, care for children with HIV, mechanism on supporting
orphans who lost their parents because of AIDS, and transmission
of the virus from mothers to children were some of the points
that panelists discussed, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Panelists said, youngsters and adults mostly contract the
disease through blood contact and sexual intercourse, but
children could be victims during pregnancy, delivery, breast
feeding and blood contact.
</P>
<P>
Children need special care as they can easily be affected by
diseases, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
