<HEADLINE> Shandong Uses World Band Loans for Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The introduction of World Bank
loans has helped promote economic development in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has promised loans of over one billion US
dollars to the province for 33 major projects, of which 843
million US dollars have already been used. Most projects funded
with the loans involve leading local industries and infrastructure
construction.
</P>
<P>
The highway linking Jinan, the provincial capital, with the
coastal city of Qingdao was constructed with a World Bank loan of
110 million US dollars. The highway, one of the province's major
traffic arteries, has increased Shandong's economic returns by
over five billion yuan (about 60 million U.S. dollars) annually.
</P>
<P>
The Zouxian Power Station, funded with a World Bank loan of 310
million US dollars, has an annual generating capacity of 7.8
billion kilowatt hours.
</P>
<P>
World Bank loans have also been used for development of the
province's agriculture, animal husbandry and aquiculture sectors,
as well as for the reclamation of polders.  
</P>
</TEXT>
