<HEADLINE> China Developing First Marine Diving Chamber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANYA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- China has developed its first
deep-sea diving compartment, which has just been tested in Sanya,
a seaside resort on the southern tip of the island province of
Hainan.
</P>
<P>
The compartment is capable of holding six divers at a time and
can be used for undersea operations 300 meters below the surface,
where it is lowered by winch to allow divers to go out to do work
and return to rest.
</P>
<P>
Divers stay in the chamber until they adjust back at the
surface. It requires a shorter adjustment time and can be used for
undersea rescue operations, salvage work, and undersea
construction work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
