<HEADLINE> Polish Government Approves Revised 1988 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The Polish government approved
the revised 1998 budget today, with a deep cut in budget deficit
set in the previous target drafted by the former government.
</P>
<P>
The revised budget deficit totals 7.7 billion zloty (2.2
billion U.S. dollars), equivalent to 1.5 percent of gross national
product (GNP).
</P>
<P>
The revenue is added by 2.3 billion zloty (650 million dollars)
while the expenditure reduced by 2.0 billion zloty ( 570 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Under the revised budget, the GNP should rise by 5.6 percent
while the inflation drop to 9.5 percent next year.
</P>
<P>
The value-added tax rate for telecommunications services,
alcohol and cigarettes will be brought up to 22 percent, 12
percent and 19 percent from 7 percent, 8 percent and 8 percent
respectively beginning next January as a measure to slash budget
deficit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
