<HEADLINE> UN Program Benefits Herdsman in World's Highest Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- A UN program near Mount
Qomolangma, the world's highest peak, has been helping herdsman
improve their harsh lives.
</P>
<P>
The three-year UNDP program started in April, 1995 with 880,000
US dollars in fund to improve the lives of the 80,000 people in a
30,000-sq.km. area.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 80,000 US dollars worth of equipment, appliances,
utensils, desks and chairs, generators, a bulldozer, and a tractor
have been provided for local families, and large numbers of
vegetables and trees planted to improve agricultural production,
according to an official in the region,
</P>
<P>
He said that work has started on water conservation projects, a
drinking water system, and two primary schools.
</P>
<P>
A half-year training class was held to teach people how to
increase incomes and the first group of 25 trainees are using
English to help foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
Some experts have drawn up plans for protecting the ecology,
developing regional tourism, and making arts and crafts in the
region, the official says.  
</P>
