Greater emphasis will also be placed on the quality of overseas
financial institutions and on a scientific risk-control and
management system.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, which is the first Chinese city to open to overseas
financial institutions, will also give the same treatment to
overseas financial institutions that it gives to Chinese ones, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Licenses have been granted to 27 overseas financial
institutions in Shenzhen, about 17 percent of the national total,
and there are 54 overseas financial institutions in Shenzhen
involved in banking, insurance, trusts, finance, and
securities. They have reported more than 300 million US in gross
profits in the past 15 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
