<HEADLINE> Brazil Urges Developed Nations to Take Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil today called on
the developed nations to take more responsibilities for global
pollution.
</P>
<P>
Brazil made the call in a proposal to be presented at an
international forum on environment. The proposal will be submitted
at the Organization of American States' (OAS) Conference on
Climatic Changes, to be held next month in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Foreign Ministry said that Brazil will propose
that actions in favor of the environment be taken with "common
responsibility".
</P>
<P>
Brazil will also suggest the setting up of a clean development
fund for environmental preservation.
</P>
<P>
Resources of the fund would be invested in non-pollutant
industrial projects in developing countries, says the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Augusto Dayrell, an official of the Foreign Ministry,
said that, at the conference, Brazil will demand industrialized
countries reduce 15 percent of carbon compounds that are going to
be thrown to the atmosphere by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
He asserted that Brazil's proposal to establish the fund is
supported by 138 nations, including the European countries, such as
Britain and Germany. 
</P>
