<HEADLINE> Tourism Becomes Fastest-Growing Industry in SW China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The growth of the tourism
sector in southwest China's Yunnan province has been quicker than
that of some traditional industries this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Economic and Technological Research Center
under the provincial government, Yunnan's annual growth rate in
the tourism sector in the past six years averaged 40 percent, 30
percentage points more than its overall economic growth rate.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate in the tourism sector was also far ahead of
that of agriculture, industry, commerce and foreign trade, whose
annual growth rates were reported at less than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, tourism had generated seven billion yuan in
profits for Yunnan, accounting for five percent of its GDP.
</P>
<P>
Tourism in Yunnan has been growing faster than tourism
nationally. In the first half of the 1990s, the annual growth rate
in the number of overseas tourists in Yunnan was 25.3 percentage
points higher than the national average. The province has now
become one of China's top ten provinces for tourism.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan has the greatest diversity of ethnic groups in China,
and is known for its natural resources and ethnic culture.
</P>
<P>
A complete tourism network of hotels, restaurants, travel
agencies, transportation, souvenirs centers, and entertainment has
been formed, with 1,000 tourist enterprises employing 160,000
people.
</P>
<P>
Officials in the center predict that Yunnan's average annual
growth of tourism in the next few years will be above 25 percent,
and its tourism sector will have 16 billion yuan in annual profits
by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
