<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
make efforts to conclude negotiations with Hungary on its EU
membership in 2000 and Britain will endeavor to speed up this
process.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook made the remark today at a
joint press conference here after meeting with his Hungarian
counterpart Kovacs Laszlo.
</P>
<P>
Cook said the British government holds that the EU should start
negotiations first with those countries that are most ready to
meet the demands and challenges of EU membership.
</P>
<P>
While not all member states agree with the approach, the issue
will be decided at an EU council meeting in Luxembourg next month.
</P>
<P>
Cook noted that Britain will hold the EU's rotating presidency
when the accession talks begin early next year.
</P>
<P>
During its presidency, Britain will take the task of
establishing the European conference, an arena for dialogue
between the EU and its membership applicants. Also the conference
will help these countries in their efforts to meet membership
qualifications.
</P>
<P>
Cook arrived here last night for a one-day visit to Hungary,
the first stop of his three-country Central Europe tour that also
includes Poland and the Czech Republic. 
