<HEADLINE> Thai Car Exports on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand exported 33,535 cars
in the first 10 months of this year with an increase of 25,097
units or 297.43 percent from the same period last year, according
to a report issued by the Federation of Thai Industries'
Automobile Industry Club available today.
</P>
<P>
The value of exported cars soared by 384.5 percent to 12.1
billion baht (318 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Though exports surged, the volume of domestically assembled
cars fell dramatically, totaling 346,561 units, down 26.27 percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thailand's exports of car engines were worth 1.73
billion baht (45.5 million dollars), an increase 179.8 percent
from the same period last year. Exports of other parts were 1.93
billion baht (50.7 million dollars), up 242.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, motorcycle exports fell by 57,721 units or 34.5
percent to 109,579. Export value dropped by 1,55 billion baht
(40.7 million dollars) or 29.6 percent to 3.69 billion baht (97.1
million dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
