<HEADLINE> Task Force Set up in Sri Lanka to Eliminate Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 27 (Xinhua) -- A National Task Force to
control the cholera epidemic was set up by the government
Wednesday, health ministry sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, eight deaths have been reported and 273 patients
have been hospitalized in North Western, Western, South, Uva and
Sabaragamuwa provinces.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic is spreading to other areas in North Central and
Central provinces.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva has instructed all
provincial health chiefs to set up diagnosis laboratories in their
respective base hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Awareness programs are being launched on a house-to-house basis
while special programs are being given to school students to
educate children about cholera.
</P>
<P>
The programs will also be launched in estates, slums and
pilgrim destinations, officials said.  
</P>
