<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Favorite To Win Player of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian striker Ronaldo stay
among the favorites to retain the world player of 1997, FIFA said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
FIFA announced that Dutchman Dennis Bergkamp, Brazil's Roberto
Carlos, Spain's Raul and Frenchman Zinedine Zidane are also the
leading candidates for the honor, which will be awarded at the
World Player Gala in Disneyland, near Paris on January 12.
</P>
<P>
The contender who will smile last will be voted out by a total
of 120 national team coaches and the winner will join Lothar
Matthaeus, Marco Van Basten, Roberto Baggio, Romario and George
Weah as the title holders.
</P>
<P>
The Gala will mark the induction of the first four players into
FIFA's International Football Hall of Champions -- Bobby Charlton,
Franz Beckenbauer, Michel Platini and Pele.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Player of the Year, the annual FIFA awards will
also include a fair play prize, team of the year and the most
improved team of the year. FIFA will announce the finalists list
on December 8. 
</P>
