<HEADLINE> Mexico`s International Reserves Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Mexico`s international
reserves dropped from 25.46 billion dollars to 25.41 billion
dollars, a loss of 50 million dollars by the end of November, the
Central Bank said today.
</P>
<P>
The bank said the drop in reserves occurred during the
third week of November, when total foreign currency reserves were
diminished by 203 million dollars to 18.17 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The bank attributed the drop in reserves to the federal
government's expenses which amounted to 286 million dollars, a
figure above the amount of foreign currencies obtained from
various means by the monetary authority of the country.
</P>
<P>
The bank also said it had an 80-million-dollar surplus,
due to recent changes in exchange rates of foreign currencies
against the dollar.
</P>
<P>
Other foreign currencies, besides the dollar, contribute to
assets and liabilities of the Bank of Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
