<HEADLINE> Trade Rises Slightly Between Brazil and Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Brazil
and the Asian countries totaled 14.61 billion U.S. dollars in the
first 10 months of 1997, one percent more than that in the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In January-October 1997, Brazil imported 7.86 billion dollars
of goods from Asian markets while the exports amounted to 6.74
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Japan, China and South Korea are the three major foreign trade
partners of Brazil, press reports quoted the Ministry of Industry,
Commerce and Tourism as saying today.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Japan exported to Brazil more than 3.4
billion dollars of goods and imported 2.62 billion dollars when
China purchased about 990 million dollars of products from Brazil
and sold 1.27 billion dollars there.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said Brazil's foreign trade with Asia reached
15.38 billion dollars last year. 
</P>
