<HEADLINE> Modern Industrial System Taking Shape in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 27 (Xinhua) -- A new industrial structure has
begun to take shape in the city of Suzhou in east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
Between 1991 and 1996, the city spent 11.7 billion yuan on six
new industries: electronic information, electronics and precision
machinery, chemicals, medicines and health care food, electrical
appliances, and new materials.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, they had 9.9 billion yuan in sales, accounting for 41
percent of the total industrial sales of the city.
</P>
<P>
They had a 9.2-billion-yuan increase in fixed assets from 1991
to 1996, and 3 billion yuan was spent on technology upgrading in
the silk industry.
</P>
<P>
The city's 20 major enterprise groups currently
account for 61 percent of its total industrial sales and 68
percent of pre-tax profits.
</P>
<P>
</P>
