<HEADLINE> Argentine Industrial Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentine industrial
production rose by 8.7 percent in the first 10 months this year
over the same period last year, the National Institute of
Statistics and Census said today.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output in October rose for the 19th consecutive
month, hitting a record growth rate of 11.2 percent compared with
a year ago.
</P>
<P>
During the January-October period, the production of chemical
products for agricultural use, cars, sugar as well as cement and
construction materials, rose by 48, 47, 44 and 26 percent
respectively from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The institute attributed this year's growth to technical
upgrading in agriculture, good weather conditions and the recovery
of the construction industry. 
</P>
