<HEADLINE> Dense Fog Causes Multi-Car Collisions in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Dense fog caused two serious
traffic accidents in the Czech Republic Tuesday. So far, one
person was reportedly killed and 18 were injuried, according to
sources
</P>
<P>
One accident involved 30 cars in multiple collisions. Because
of the heavy fog at 8 a.m., cars kept colliding with each other on
the number 1 expressway from Brno to Prague.
</P>
<P>
Four hours later, fifteen autos were involved in a similar
collision on the same road. The ensuing traffic jams lasted for
several hours.
</P>
<P>
The two accidents were reportedly among the most serious in the
country in recent years. Direct losses amounted to about 10
million koruna (about 303,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The accidents were attributed to heavy fog and cars traveling
at a rate of speed too high for prevailing conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
