<HEADLINE> Central China Province Improves Water-Related Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province's economy is
growing because of the speedy development of local water-related
industries.
</P>
<P>
The province has gained 3.5 billion yuan from water-related
industries, of which 270 million yuan is pre-tax profit.
</P>
<P>
Henan has 13 cities and counties with earnings from
water-related industries surpassing 100 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The province has focused on improving and increasing water
supply, particularly in urban areas for industrial use.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 water-supply projects have been completed in
local urban and rural areas, providing 2.5 billion cubic meters
for industrial production and residents.
</P>
<P>
Among the 18 big reservoirs under the management of the
province, nine have been equipped with systems which can help
provide more than 400 million cubic meters of water for industrial
production and residents.
</P>
<P>
The province has also built amusement parks and entertainment
centers on water.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the output of aquatic products in the province
reached 202,000 tons, bringing in nearly 1.6 billion yuan in
output value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
