<HEADLINE> Mexico Hosts Attorneys General Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Association of Courts of General Sessions opened a forum here
today to discuss the structure, jurisdiction and procedure of more
than 30 courts.
</P>
<P>
The two-day forum was attended by attorneys general and
judicial delegates from 31 countries in America and Europe.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss international legal cooperation, fight
against drug trafficking and organized crime, actions against
corruption, and crimes related to environmental deterioration.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also analyze the system of penal prosecution,
organization of courts of general sessions in participating
countries, and international extradition treaties.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-American Association of Courts of General Sessions
was set up in November 1954 in Brazil and has since been joined by
all American countries. 
