<HEADLINE> Local Yamaichi Financial Standing Intact: Auditors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Auditors of Yamaichi (Phils.)
Inc. said the local subsidiary of Japan's Yamaichi Securities Co
Ltd. is still financially viable to continue with its local
operations.
</P>
<P>
Auditors from both the Philippine Stock Exchange (PSE) and the
Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) said that the brokerage
house is in good financial standing and that it has had no
violations.
</P>
<P>
"The firm has no violations at all and is very liquid.
Furthermore, all its financial and transaction records are in
order," local newspaper The Manila Chronicle today quoted auditors
as saying.
</P>
<P>
PSE officials also disclosed that the local affiliate has more
than 110 million pesos (3.2 million US dollars) in cash, which can
be used to pay its investors if necessary.
</P>
<P>
For its part, the PSE said it sees no need to interfere in
Yamaichi's local operations, unless its bankrupt parent company in
Japan decides to liquidate its equity and sell its PSE membership
seat.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the SEC, after visiting Yamaichi's office
to determine the real financial status of the firm, also said
everything is in order.
</P>
<P>
The local trading arm of Yamaichi Securities Co. Ltd. stopped
operations since Monday after the collapse of its parent firm in
Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
