<HEADLINE> Ostersund Seeks Support To Revive Olympic Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Ostersund placed its hope on
the Swedish sports groups on Thursday after it failed to win
support from the Swedish Olympic Committee (SOC) in a bid for the
2006 Winter Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The SOC board has voted not to back the Swedish town in its
fourth consecutive Olympic bid.
</P>
<P>
Ostersund has appealed to the SOC for reconsideration of the
decision at its joint annual general meeting with Sweden's Olympic
sports federations scheduled on Thursday in Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
The sports federations could reverse the decision with a
majority vote.
</P>
<P>
The SOC listed lack of improvements in the bid as the top
reason for giving the thumbs-down.
</P>
<P>
Ostersund lost to Lillehammer for the 1994 Winter Games by only
a few votes and its bids failed again in 1998 and 2002.
</P>
<P>
Statements of interest should be submitted to the International
Olympic Committee by February 1 next year, with final bids expire
by September. 
</P>
