<HEADLINE> Czech Republic Increases Housing Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Housing construction in the
Czech Republic has recovered from a serious slump; a large number
of apartments have been completed during the first three quarters
of this year, a spokesman for the Ministry of Regional Development
and Housing said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that during the first three months of this
year, 9,500 apartments were made available to tenants, up 20
percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
During this year so far, about 86,000 apartments were
reportedly under construction, an increase of 17 percent from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Within the past few years, however, housing construction has
been in a major slump as a result of money shortages.
</P>
<P>
Although housing projects have been increased, the supply falls
short of demand, according to the spokesman. Some big cities are
still confronted with the lack of adequate and sufficient
housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
