<HEADLINE> Chilean Minister Assesses Asian Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, November 26 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Finance Minister
Eduardo Animat today ruled out the possibility that the financial
crisis in Southeast Asia would affect Chile's national budget for
1998.
</P>
<P>
But the crisis is likely to make an impact on the trading
balance, he added.
</P>
<P>
He was confident that the crisis is temporary and will not
produce serious consequences for Chile.
</P>
<P>
