<HEADLINE> Shanghai Computerizing Service Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, November 27 (Xinhua) -- China's leading industrial
city is making an effort to computerize the service business in
Shanghai's development zone, the Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech project is expected to complete a computerized
network that links all financial organizations with enterprises
and government departments in the zone by the year 2000 to allow
business transactions to be done via the network.
</P>
<P>
Big department stores have also begun to provide multi-media
shopping guides and long-distance computerized purchase systems,
and 90 percent of the city's chain-stores are already connected to
a computerized network.
</P>
<P>
The wider use of computerized cash registers has allowed the
greater use of credit cards.
</P>
<P>
The computer project also involves computerizing business
between export-oriented companies and in the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
An economic information network will link government
departments to development zones and enterprises and is expected
to provide information for cities along the Yangtze River via the
VSAT satellite system.
</P>
<P>
An electronic system combining telephones, TVs, and computers
is also under construction in some parts of the city.  
</P>
