<HEADLINE> East China Province Promotes Development of Large Agricultural Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- The government of east China's
Shandong Province recently revealed a plan to back 50 major
agricultural enterprises to speed up the industrialization of
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The 50 enterprises are involved in agriculture, forestry,
animal husbandry and the aquatic industry, and had total assets
of 14 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will help them get a larger share of
the domestic market, according to a government official, and
they are expected to have annual sales exceeding 500 million yuan
each.
</P>
<P>
Their total exports are expected to be 2 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
