<HEADLINE> Rasmussen to Move to England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 27 (Xinhua) -- World badminton champion Peter
Rasmussen of Denmark is planning to move to Britain in January,
the Badminton Association of England (BAE) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
BAE association said Rasmussen would look for a house near the
BAE headquarters in Milton Keynes.
</P>
<P>
Rasmussen hopes to train at the National Badminton Center with
England's elite squad and with compatriot Poul-Eric Hoyer-Larsen,
who lives near there. 
