<HEADLINE> Jansher Crashed in Qatar Squash International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 26 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan of
Pakistan was crashed out of the Qatar Squash International
Tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jansher lost to fourth seed Canadian Jonathon Power 15-14, 15-6
and 15-2 in a semi-final match. Power will meet third-seeded Scot
Peter Nicol in Thursday's final after Nical beat second-seeded
Australian Rodney Eyles 17-16, 15-7 and 15-10.
</P>
<P>
Nicol's win saw him reverse a loss to Eyles in the World Open
final in Kuala Lumpur earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Power became only the 15th player to beat Jansher in more than
10 years and it was only the Pakistani's 50th defeat in all
competitions since he first set out on the PSA World Tour as a
17-year-old.
</P>
<P>
Jansher has won 89 major titles since then, but refused to
defend his world crown in Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
