<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Doing Well in Saving Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, November 27 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province, one of the
country's traditional industrial bases, has achieved a great deal
in economizing energy consumption during 1991-1995.
</P>
<P>
Local energy consumption for every 10,000-yuan GNP during the
period dropped 32 percent from the previous five-year period. In
the past, local energy consumption was much higher than the
national average.
</P>
<P>
Jilin, with heavy industry contributing 70 percent of the local
economy, has 643 large- and medium-size industrial enterprises.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1995 period, the province saved 4.5 million
tons of standard coal in energy, one of the reasons for a 64
percent rise in local industrial output from the previous five
years.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the province allocated special funds for energy-saving,
which will be used for an energy-efficient lighting project and
for technological improvements.
</P>
<P>
Jilin spent nearly 1.2 billion yuan on basic construction and
technological improvements for saving energy during the 1991-1995
period.
</P>
<P>
It also resorted to economic levers such as pricing, credit,
taxes and depreciation to encourage local enterprises to improve
energy efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The province also placed more effort on the development and use
of bio-gas, solar energy and wind power and has built up a number
of small hydropower stations with installed capacity totalling
65,000 kilowatts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
