<HEADLINE> EU: WTO Takes Positive View on EU's Trade Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Trade Organization
(WTO) has taken a positive view on the European Union's trade
policy, said a EU official in charge of WTO questions here today.
</P>
<P>
Herve Jouanjean, director of WTO questions at the European
Commission, commended the EU's commitment to the WTO-based trading
system and its leadership role in both ongoing negotiations and in
seeking further trade liberalization.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the results of the WTO's biennial assessment, he
said that the review had confirmed the essentially open looking
path taken by the EU in its trade policies.
</P>
<P>
"Overall, the WTO has given a strong endorsement to the EU's
trade policies and our commitment to future liberalization,"
Jouanjean told reporters at the press conference held at the end
of the two-day review of the EU's trade policy on November 25-26.
</P>
<P>
"Traditional areas of concern were not ignored, but the review
was able to look at the wood as a whole, and not just the trees,"
he said. "At the same time it has underlined its view that, the
EU, as the world's largest trading entity, has a particular
responsibility towards the multilateral system, and that we must
continue down the outward looking path we have taken."
</P>
<P>
"In our view, with the in-built work program of the WTO, and
with the decisions taken by ministers in Singapore, we have an
unparalleled opportunity for further trade liberalization, which
must be tackled in a comprehensive way," Jouanjean said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
